input_str: Despite rumors to the contrary, April 3, 2004, wasn’t the day that the music died in Tempe. It was, however, when the plug was pulled on fabled Mill Avenue rock club Long Wong’s, a heartbreaking event that may have signaled the end of an era but wasn’t a death knell for the city’s live music scene. Nor were any of the closures that shuttered several prominent Tempe venues
